page.title: 12ECOLOGY
page.content: IN SHELDONDALE WE PASS GARLIC & VIOLET BANKS ON RIGHT,A PATCH OF ORCHIDS ON LEFT AT THE BOTTOM OF KIRKDALE; TO BAKEWELL GATE PAST WILD ROSE,RASPBERRY SCABIOUS,GERANIUM,WILLOWHERB,THISTLE & COMFREY;TO THE LEFT HAGE LANE WITH HOLLY,BLACKBERRY,HAREBELL,ROSE, SCABIOUS,WOODY NIGHTSHADE & BELOW THAT TOWARDS LOWER FARM & ON LEFT COWSLIP FIELD WITH ORCHID ON VERGE.FROM FARM BACK DOWN FIELD TO STILE TO ORCHID, YELLOW PANSY & DOG DAISY,THROUGH SHACK LOW WOOD PAST BLUEBELL,WOOD ANEMONE, LILY-OF-THE-VALLEY,RAGGED ROBIN,GARLIC PRIMROSE,WATER AVENS,ARUM TO NETTLER DALE.WILD STONECROP IN DIP AT TOP OF VILLAGE & VAST NUMBERS OF SMALLER FLOWERS.AT ONCE A WEEK PLANTING,ERICA COWSLIP,RATTLEGRASS,PANSIES,VIOLET. YELLOW PANSIES & MUSHROOMS AT MAGPIE MINE BUT ONLY SYCAMORE,ASH & HAWTHORN TREES THRIVE.
